sudo apt update
sudo apt-get update -y
apt install perl -y
apt list --installed | grep -i perl
sudo apt install make
sudo apt-get install -y perl-tk

cpan
install Parallel::ForkManager
install String::Util
install Net::SIP

his module can be installed on perl5.8 if you add Net::DNS.
حمل المكتبات
Net::SIP:::SocketPool    بهيك طريقة
It was not tested on older versions but it might work if you add
Storable, List::Util, Hash::Util, Time::HiRes, Digest::MD5
and IO::Socket.
cpan Net::SIP:::SocketPool
use Data::Dumper;
use IO::Socket::INET;
use Socket;
use Test::More;
use Net::SIP;
use Parallel::ForkManager;
use Term::ANSIColor;
use Time::HiRes qw(gettimeofday tv_interval);

The module itself is pure perl, so if the prerequisites are
fullfilled no C-Compiler is necessary.

For installation do the usual

	perl Makefile.PL
	make
	make test
	make install
  
